The form path builds pending_mrr_data with available_qty: "N/A" hardcoded (I put that in the spec as a placeholder since the form doesn't do a live inventory check). Fix: when building pending_mrr_data in form_submit_handler, query com_search.QOH for each item (same table we already query for price). One extra field from the same SELECT.
Bug 2 — Need by date and return date displaying incorrectly.
Likely a datetime format issue — dates coming as Python datetime objects or ISO strings with timestamps (2026-06-03T00:00:00) instead of clean YYYY-MM-DD. Fix: normalize all date fields to YYYY-MM-DD string when building pending_mrr_data and in _build_mrr_preview_message.
Bug 3 — Financial year in MRR number (25-26 hardcoded, should be dynamic).
Current code has f"MRR/{next_id}/25-26" hardcoded in multiple places. Fix: compute current FY dynamically — if current month >= April, FY is {year}-{year+1}, else {year-1}-{year}. E.g., June 2026 → FY 26-27. Need to find ALL places where the MRR number is built and fix consistently. This may be in form_submit_handler_node, evaluate_and_route, and possibly mrr_submission_node.
